        <a class='permalink' href='#S6CV0340P0_19991209_WH_76' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        5.9 pm
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0340P0_19991209_WH_77'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-graham-stringer' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0340P0_19991209_WH_77' title='Link to this speech by Mr Graham Stringer' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-graham-stringer" title="Mr Graham Stringer">The Parliamentary Secretary, Cabinet Office (Mr. Graham Stringer)</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            I am pleased to be speaking for the first time in this Room and to reply in a Government-sponsored debate. I hope that you will know when I am standing and sitting, Mr. Deputy Speaker. I shall do my best to ensure that you do.</p><p>
            I spent much of my adult life in a horseshoe-shaped chamber and it does not necessarily lead to consensus. In Manchester city council I participated in debates that were at least as vicious as the most vicious debates in the House&#x2014;
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0340P0_19991209_WH_78'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-ian-mccartney' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0340P0_19991209_WH_78' title='Link to this speech by Mr Ian McCartney' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-ian-mccartney" title="Mr Ian McCartney">Mr. Ian McCartney</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            And that was just in the Labour group.
          </p>
